  "texts": [
    "A trial is only considered successful if the generated test case builds, passes, and increases coverage over all existing test cases.",
    "As can be seen, the success rate is similar for both platforms, although slightly higher for Facebook than for Instagram.",
    "We believe that this difference may be due to the difference in available training data.",
    "There is approximately one order of magnitude more human-written Kotlin test code for Facebook then there is for Instagram.Temperature Successful Total Success trials trials rate 0.9 50 1,580 0.03 0.8 18 703 0.03 0.7 12 552 0.02 0.6 7 536 0.01 0.5 4 500 0.01 0.4 16 334 0.05 0.3 5 324 0.02 0.2 3 505 0.01 0.1 4 552 0.01 0.0 1,215 30,483 0.04 Table 4: Results for different temperature settings.",
    "After initial experimentation, zero was chosen as the default, hence its far greater number of overall trials.Table 4 shows the performance over both language models and all four prompts for different temperature settings."
